Any attempt to frustrate and delay the passage of this year’s budget will be resisted by APC senators , a former Senate Leader, Ali Ndume said yesterday. Recall that a mild drama played out at the National Assembly on December 19 last year when President Muhammadu Buhari presented the budget proposal to joint session of the legislature. While APC lawmakers sang the President’s praises, those in the opposition tongue-lashed him. Speaking after a meeting with the president at the State House Villa, Abuja, together with the Taraba governorship candidate of the APC, Sani Abubakar, Ndume said the fiscal document will be passed as soon as possible. 10 events that shaped Senate in 2017 MTEF: FG, NASS to resolve impasse  this week Ekweremadu: South-East Reps to hold Ndume responsible